{{Infobox scientist | honorific_prefix = | name = Alan Lizotte | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | image_size = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | birth_place = | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | pronounce = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = American | fields = [[Criminology]] | workplaces = [[University at Albany]] | patrons = | education = [[Brown University]], [[University of Illinois]] | alma_mater = | thesis_title = Patterns of Firearms Ownership in Illinois | thesis_url = https://www.ideals.illinois.edu/handle/2142/67896 | thesis_year = 1979 | doctoral_advisor = <!--(or | doctoral_advisors = )--> | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = 2003 [[Michael J. Hindelang Award]] | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }} '''Alan Jeffrey Lizotte''' is an American criminologist and Distinguished Professor in the [[University at Albany, SUNY School of Criminal Justice|School of Criminal Justice]] at the [[University at Albany]]. ==Early life and education== Lizotte grew up in [[Grand Junction, Colorado]], where he later recalled almost everyone he knew owning a gun.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/07/23/politics/obama-romney-guns/index.html |title=Little to gain, lots to lose for Obama and Romney on guns - CNNPolitics |last=Abdullah |first=Halimah |date=2012-07-23 |work=CNN |access-date=2017-12-27}}</ref> He served in the [[United States Navy]] from July 1966 to January 1970. His service included one tour on the [[USS Jouett (CG-29)|USS Jouett]] in the [[Vietnam War]], and one-and-a-half tours in the Inshore Undersea Warfare Group One, Unit 2, on land; he attained the rank of [[Petty officer second class|Second Class Petty Officer]] as a [[radioman]] before being discharged.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.albany.edu/alumni-vets/lizotte.php |title=Alan J. Lizotte |website=Alumni Vets|publisher=University at Albany-SUNY |language=en |access-date=2017-12-27}}</ref> He later received his bachelor's degree in [[sociology]] from [[Brown University]] in 1974, followed by a M.A. (1976) and Ph.D. (1979) from the [[University of Illinois]], also in sociology.<ref name=cv>{{Cite web |url=https://www.albany.edu/scj/files/LizotteA.pdf |title=Alan Lizotte CV}}</ref> As a grad student at the University of Illinois, he shared an office with [[Gary Kleck]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/magazine/1998/03/29/trigger-points/414dea7f-6320-4537-ad15-1e642187a1f4/ |title=TRIGGER POINTS |last=Thompson |first=Bob |date=1998-03-29 |work=Washington Post |access-date=2017-12-27 |language=en-US |issn=0190-8286}}</ref>
==Career== Lizotte was an assistant professor of sociology at [[Emory University]] from 1978 to 1980. He first joined the faculty of the University at Albany's School of Criminal Justice in 1985 as an associate professor, and was named a full professor there in 1993. In 2016, he became a Distinguished Professor at the School.<ref name=cv/> He served as the director of the School's Hindelang Criminal Justice Research Center from 1994 to 1997, and then again from 2003 to 2010, when he was named the School's dean; he retained the latter position until 2015.<ref name=cv/><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.albany.edu/news/82547.php |title=A Gift for Preeminence |date=2017-10-23 |work=University at Albany |access-date=2017-12-27 |language=en}}</ref> From 2004 to 2007, he was an executive counselor for the [[American Society of Criminology]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.albany.edu/news/release_9105.php |title=National Gun Control Expert Alan Lizotte Appointed Dean of UAlbany's Top-Ranked School of Criminal Justice - University at Albany-SUNY |date=2010-03-04 |website=University at Albany |language=en |access-date=2017-12-27}}</ref> ==Honors and awards== In 2003, Lizotte received the [[Michael J. Hindelang Award]] from the American Society of Criminology, and in 2014, he was named one of its fellows.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.albany.edu/news/50440.php |title=Dean Alan Lizotte Named Fellow of American Society of Criminology |date=2014-05-21 |website=University at Albany |language=en |access-date=2017-12-27}}</ref> ==References== {{Reflist}} {{Authority control}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Lizotte, Alan Jeffrey}}
