The '''Catholic Club''' in [[Bangalore]] is a [[Social club|social association]] established by Bangalore [[Catholic]] [[Archdiocese of Bangalore|Archdiocese]] in 1948,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.india9.com/i9show/Catholic-Club-50490.htm|title=Catholic Club|date=31 October 2017 | publisher=India9|accessdate=8 July 2018 }}</ref> although its membership is not limited to Catholics. The club-house is located on [[Museum Road]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/11/11/stories/2006111120860400.htm|title=The pride of Bangalore|date=11 November 2006|work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=18 March 2013}}</ref> next to St. Patrick's church. The Catholic Club is notable for its Christmas ball and New Year's [[Ball (dance)|ball]].

