The '''Imperial Regalia of Brazil''' consists of the Imperial Crowns: the [[Imperial Crown of Brazil|Crown of Pedro II]] and the Crown of Pedro I; the Imperial Sceptre; the Imperial Orb; the Imperial Sword; and jewelry belonging to the Emperors and Empresses of [[Brazil]]. They were used until the abolition of the [[Empire of Brazil|Brazilian monarchy]] in 1889. Most of the jewels have been  displayed at the [[Imperial Museum of Brazil]] in [[Petrópolis]] and at the [[National Museum of Brazil]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] since 1943.<ref name="b"/> Other items are stored at the [[National Treasury of Brazil|National Treasury]] in [[Brasília]].

