'''''Mwami''''' ({{IPA-rw|mwɑmi, mŋɑmi|pron}}) is the chiefly title in [[Kirundi]] and [[Kinyarwanda]], the Congolese [[Nande language|Nande]] and Bashi languages, [[Luhya language|Luhya]] in [[Kenya]] and various other Bantu languages, such as the Tonga language (spoken in Zambia and Zimbabwe). The word is usually translated as ''king''.  It can refer to:

* the [[King of Rwanda]]
* the [[King of Burundi]]
* the traditional chiefs of the small kingdoms in the [[Nord-Kivu]], [[Sud-Kivu]] and [[Maniema]] provinces in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]
* the traditional chiefs of the "Bantu Botatwe" (three peoples) of Zambia (namely, the Ila, the Lenje and the [[Tonga people|Tonga]] peoples)

